As she races to the most important job interview of her life, she finds herself among drug dealers and hookers — all while being pursued by the LAPD, an angry taxi driver, and a young kid with an attitude.

Boy's other hero, his father, Alamein, is the subject of Boy's fantasies, and he imagines him as a deep sea diver, war hero and a close relation of Michael Jackson (he can even dance like him). The Dicksons are struggling through major life changes together all the while trying desperately to emerge intact on the other side. For this family, just getting through the day is a win. Bad hair day? Nope! More like a bad hair life."

The Duke’s conniving nephew believes the two to be a royal pain and will stop at no cost to steal the inheritance, even if it means marrying into the “Dukedome” via their pet poodle. A dog’s tale of love and devotion that will have your family sitting up and begging for more!

programme.title: Eighteam

All passengers, including 18 players, die in the accident.The Chipolopolo's captain, Kalusha Bwalya, who is not aboard the ill-fated flight puts his efforts to build a new team and make a professional federation becoming later the national team coach and president of the Football Association of Zambia. programme.title: Break Point: a Davis Cup Story

The team’s number two player, Roberto Bautista, had to leave the competition for his hometown to be at his father´s side during the last hours of his life. Without Bautista, Nadal and Feliciano López heroically managed to lead the team into the final. But then came the news that thrilled tennis fans worldwide: Bautista is coming back to the competition after his father´s funeral, and he´s ready to play. programme.title: The Royal Bodyguard: The Limping Assassin S01 E01
programme.desc: It’s the Commonwealth Conference in Scotland, but there’s intelligence that suggests a planned assassination attempt on The Queen. Taking his new role very seriously, Hubble soon manages to upset foreign ambassadors, colleagues, hotel guests and even the restaurant pianist as he haphazardly carries out his security checks. An attractive woman spells trouble as he gives away vital security information – and soon has to go all out to save her Majesty

programme.title: The Royal Bodyguard: Bullets Over Broad Street S01 E02
programme.desc: Hubble enlists the help of his aspirant sniffer dog Winston as he continues in his new role of Royal Bodyguard. It’s the Queen’s birthday, but Hubble soon stumbles into calamity and is forced to take a few days break at a health spa – where he comes across a familiar face and his planned relaxation is suddenly shelved. Hubble returns to duty in time to oversee Her Majesty’s visit to an Oxford Museum, which is far from straightforward.

programme.title: The Royal Bodyguard: The Siege of Blenheim Square S01 E03
programme.desc: A routine shopping trip for a Prince turns into a potentially dangerous siege after a misunderstanding between Hubble and a member of the Prince’s protection team. As negotiations get underway Hubble only seems to be able to worsen the situation. Despite this, he plans his own personal rescue mission.

programme.title: The Royal Bodyguard: The Royal Art of Blackmail S01 E04
programme.desc: There’s been a burglary at the Palace and The Queen enlists Hubble to source its culprit. But there is more concern when it appears that the thieves were unwittingly assisted by Hubble, much to Dennis’s joy.David Walliams (Little Britain, Come Fly with Me) joins us in this episode. Guy’s endeavours to make things right put him in a sticky situation.

programme.title: The Royal Bodyguard: The Perils of Attraction S01 E05
programme.desc: Hubble adopts a new persona to root out a mole at Number 10, but his performance is perhaps too convincing, as he bewitches a new colleague and upsets his superior’s wife.

programme.title: The Royal Bodyguard: A Watery Grave S01 E06
programme.desc: The Princess is on her hen do. Hubble is put in charge of security and loses her after an aggressive assault from a gaggle of hen-nighters. Soon there is another mysterious attack with a stone gargoyle. Hubble fears for his life and Yates is employed as his bodyguard. But strange things continue to happen...

programme.title: Soundtrack to Sixteen
programme.desc: Soundtrack to Sixteen is a coming-of-age film about two anxious teens growing up in London in the 2000s. Maisy is self-conscious and constantly overanalysing. She is obsessed with having her first kiss this year, before she turns seventeen, but stalking the boy next door doesn't seem to be working. Meanwhile Ben, a boy from a nearby school, is happy being a nerd and thinking he's better than everyone else until his grades start plummeting. For the first time he must come face to face with the idea that he might, in fact, be average. When the two meet each other on the night bus things get even more confusing for them as they attempt to navigate their first potential romance under the stress of exams that will define their future.

programme.title: Colossal Youth
programme.desc: Colossal Youth follows four friends Ryder (Troy Osterberg), Greg (Riker Lynch), Erica (Kimmy Caruso) and Jordan (Reese Everett Ryan) as they navigate life, love and the wild and crazy times of high school. Ryder is a hopeless romantic and when his dream girl obsession Siobhan (Alexa Dowd) returns to school he goes for broke trying to win her heart. His pursuits lead him to rock bottom, but it's there that he realizes his real love has been beside him all along.
